name 'U2L08 Free Response 3'
title 'Router Table: Reflection'


markdown <<MARKDOWN
Why does a router keep track of the cost to a destination through multiple routers instead of only the fastest one?

MARKDOWN

teacher_markdown <<MARKDOWN
Should a line go down a router will want to know what the next best option for sending a packet might be. Keeping track of multiple connections allows a router to be flexible as the condition of a network changes.
MARKDOWN
